First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 12:10 PM ET
Banks

Company Overview of First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company



Snapshot People




Company Overview
First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company, a state-chartered commercial bank, provides banking services to individuals, businesses, professionals, and the medical community. It offers personal banking services, including checking accounts, savings accounts and CDs, debit cards, and online and mobile banking; loans and credit services, such as credit cards, home equity loans and lines of credit, mortgage loans, refinancing, auto loans, and other personal loans and lines of credit; online and mobile services; insurance products and services; and investments and retirement, including individual retirement accounts and retirement planning. The company’s business products and services include banking, ...
First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company, a state-chartered commercial bank, provides banking services to individuals, businesses, professionals, and the medical community. It offers personal banking services, including checking accounts, savings accounts and CDs, debit cards, and online and mobile banking; loans and credit services, such as credit cards, home equity loans and lines of credit, mortgage loans, refinancing, auto loans, and other personal loans and lines of credit; online and mobile services; insurance products and services; and investments and retirement, including individual retirement accounts and retirement planning. The company’s business products and services include banking, payment acceptance, equipment finance and leasing, insurance, and online payroll; business checking accounts, business online banking, business debit cards, business credit cards, merchant services, and business savings accounts and CDs; credit and financing services, such as equipment financing and leasing, business lines of credit, and business loans; cash management services, including merchant card processing, payroll solutions, remote image deposits, manage payables, manage receivables, liquidity management, reconciliation and reporting, and fraud prevention; and insurance products and services. First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company was formerly known as Bank of Smithfield and changed its name to First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company in 1929. The company was founded in 1898 and is based in Raleigh, North Carolina. It has branches in Arizona, California, Colorado, District of Columbia, Florida, Georgia, Kansas, Maryland, Missouri, New Mexico, North Carolina, Oklahoma, Oregon, South Carolina, Tennessee, Texas, Virginia, Washington, and West Virginia. First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company operates as a subsidiary of First Citizens Bancshares Inc.
Detailed Description


239 Fayetteville StreetWake CountyRaleigh, NC 27601United StatesFounded in 1898



